the firms latest securities and exchange commission filings the ucits strategy is similar to clinton groups equity strategies hedge fund which had  million at yearend making it the firms largest fund it too has also suffered sizeable performance losses clinton group declined to comment for this story last year clinton groups assets  which once stood at more than  billion  had reached their highest level in a decade as the firm sought to come back from an earlier valuation scandal and problems associated with the financial crisis at the end of  it reported  billion in regulatory assets under management though that number also includes leverage the recent decline is a combination of redemptions and performance losses investors say a big chunk of these redemptions occurred in may when the ucits fund lost more than  percent bringing its year to date loss to  percent according to the deutsche report last year it lost  percent its only winning year was in  when it was launched the ucits fund was launched in may of  and gained  percent that year most of its holdings are european stocks its unclear how much leverage compounded the woes but the ucits gross leverage was not expected to exceed  percent of the value of the fund according to deutsche bank while the us quant funds composition is similar to the ucits investors cant sell their shares as easily as in the ucits which has daily liquidity the us quant fund which has been around much longer has produced annualized returns of  percent since inception in  according to the deutsche report still that is down from about  percent last september even before the latest troubles clinton was a shadow of its former self hall was one of the more flamboyant figures in the hedge fund world more than a decade ago he even merited a mention in a  new york magazine story about hedge funds that wrote about his foot yacht anchored for a time in chelsea piers clinton which opened its doors in  was once one of the biggest hedge fund firms in the business focusing on convertible bonds and mortgagebacked securities by  it was running about  billion then an exemployee sued the firm charging it with mismarking its assetbacked securities both the commodities and futures trading commission and the securities and exchange commission investigated but declined to bring any action against clinton but assets fell to about  billion despite the clean bill of health  in early  clintons assets fell to a new low of  million after its multistrategy fund fell  percent due to bad bets on mortgagebacked securities according to a bloomberg report total assets in that fund declined by almost  percent due to redemptions since the financial crisis clinton fashioned a comeback with its move into quants a strategy run by yong lu a physics phd who joined clinton as senior portfolio manager in  from citadel separately in june the yearold hall put his manhattan townhouse on the market asking  million for his  east th street pad according to city records reported by real estate website luxury living nyc he paid  million for the home which has seven bedrooms and more than five bathrooms hall bought the house in  when he was one of the top hedge fund moguls in the us sponsored video get started subscribe show me all of my options   research  rankings competition heats up among asian executives taiwan semiconductor manufacturing co was the only firm to sweep its industry in institutional  the  emea sales team  voters praise the bank’s emea equity sales team for its accessibility and transparency ranking  the  emea research team  for a fifth straight year bank of america is no  in institutional investor’s  the  allasia sales team  credit suisse unseats twotime champion morgan stanley in our sixthannual ranking of the region’s  browse rankings select report type executive teams research sales  trading the world’s best hotels top money managers select ranking search see more research  rankings »   institutional investor llc 