may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view filson company  wikipedia filson company from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search cc filson inc type private industry luggage manufacturing clothing manufacturing retail wholesale predecessor cc filsons pioneer alaska clothing and blanket manufacturers founded seattle washington united states   founder clinton c filson headquarters seattle washington united states number of locations  companyoperated stores and  manufacturing locations area served worldwide products luggage apparel services clothing repair clothing rewaxing parent bedrock manufacturing co subsidiaries cc filson co website filsoncom cc filson is a seattle washingtonbased privately owned outfitter and manufacturer of goods for outdoor enthusiasts the company designs manufactures distributes and sells mens and womens outdoor clothing accessories and luggage filson sells its products via companyowned retail stores catalogs and the filson website as well as through authorized dealers in the united states and international distributors the company was originally established in seattle in  as cc filsons pioneer alaska clothing and blanket manufacturers to meet the needs of prospectors passing through seattle on their way to the klondike gold rush as of  the brand is owned by bedrock manufacturing founder tom kartsotis who also owns shinola contents  early history  ownership and leadership  retail locations  modern product line  references  external links early historyedit clinton c filson born  a former nebraska homesteader and railroad conductor moved to seattle washington in the s where he operated a small loggers outfitting store to meet the needs of prospectors passing through seattle on their way to the klondike gold rush cc filson founded cc filsons pioneer alaska clothing and blanket manufacturers in  the company supplied prospectors with a variety of outdoor gear including clothing blankets boots and sleeping bags after the gold rush ended around  filson shifted to providing gear for outdoor oriented activities and occupations including hunting fishing and logging among others ownership and leadershipedit filson remained under the control of the filson family until  when they sold their interest to a former distributor of filson products to independent dealers in alaska stan kohls a skiwear entrepreneur purchased the company in  kohls expanded the product line from  items to  items drawing from the companys archive or designing each new item himself kohls attempted to preserve the authenticity of the products by not using modern materials like velcro on january   los angeles californiabased private equity group brentwood associates and former polo ralph lauren corporation executive doug williams acquired cc filson with kohls maintaining a minority ownership interest and a seat on the board brentwood associates and williams renamed the company filson holdings and named williams the chief executive officer williams hoped to expand the brands sales by introducing casual wear and selling to new customers based on filsons reputation for ruggedness and quality in  filson made bill kulczycki a former patagonia executive ceo in  mark a korros became ceo in  brentwood associates sold filson holdings inc to dallasbased bedrock manufacturing co for an undisclosed amount alan kirk was appointed ceo of filson in  in june  the company opened an extensive new manufacturing facility on st avenue south in seattles manufacturing district more than doubling capacity and by year end more than  new jobs were created in production the company now manufactures luggage apparel and accessories in three companyowned locations in the usa the current filson president is gray madden who is lead the charge on the construction of a brandnew squarefoot flagship store in its current headquarters at  first ave s in seattle when customers enter the building they see workers manufacturing filsons luggage products on the first floor the store on the second floor has clear glass doors that showcase office space where the companys creative teams are coming up with the next big idea retail locationsedit in addition to the companys retail website filson products are available for sale at flagship stores in seattle minneapolis new york austin portland washington dc london dallas san francisco plano and detroit filson will open its first canadian location this march in vancouver each is located in affluent shopping districts and neighborhoods outlet stores are located in eagan minnesota and burlington washington modern product lineedit in  filson revived its line of bridle leathertrimmed canvas luggage in  filson opened a flagship retail store near seattles safeco field in  filson introduced a line of womens clothing in  filson partnered with levi strauss  co to produce a collection of jackets shirts caps and bags called levi’s workwear by filson referencesedit  stacy perman the real history of americas most authentic fake brand inc magazine p  april   a b c d bourjaily phil october   fear of fashion cnn money cable news network oclc  archived from the original on august   retrieved august   clinton c filson founded the company in  to outfit prospectors headed for the klondikewilliams is betting that people who own filson hunting clothes will also buy filson casual wear and that others will discover the brand as they learn of its reputation for ruggedness and quality   a b filsons history filson cc filson co archived from the original on august   retrieved august   the gold rush faded into history but filson kept listening to his customers and outdoorsmen kept coming to filson for rugged clothes drawing from his past experience outfitting loggers he soon added clothing for